  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "The legal framework surrounding money laundering involves several key components:\n\n1. International Regulations\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) guidelines\n- United Nations Conventions\n- Basel Committee recommendations\n\n2. Domestic Legislation\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) laws\n- Bank Secrecy Act\n- Proceeds of Crime legislation\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) requirements\n\n3. Key Legal Principles\n- Criminalizing money laundering activities\n- Mandatory reporting of suspicious transactions\n- Enhanced due diligence requirements\n- Asset seizure and forfeiture provisions\n\n4. Regulatory Bodies\n- Financial intelligence units\n- Banking regulators\n- Law enforcement agencies\n- Judicial systems\n\n5. Compliance Requirements\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Customer identification procedures\n- Risk assessment protocols\n- Reporting suspicious activities\n\n6. Penalties\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Significant financial penalties\n- Professional license revocation\n- Asset freezing/confiscation\n\n7. International Cooperation\n- Information sharing agreements\n- Extradition treaties\n- Cross-border investigation mechanisms\n\nThe framework aims to prevent, detect, and prosecute financial crimes and terrorist financing.",
